metadata.name: Monsoon #85
metadata.description:
Optimization. It's something that haunts all programmers. Including me. But no longer! Monsoon is a study into the optimization of particle systems for the web. Looking especially deep into dynamic grids and dynamic frame rates.

As for the piece itself, it's a reference to how busy this modern world is. How we're all constantly on the go, whether that is physically, or mentally. Almost feeling like a monsoon. A storm of information. A storm of life. A storm of work. A storm of thoughts. A storm of emotions. A storm of everything. And it's all so fast.

As are the particles. They're all moving around these cyclones of information. Glowing up like neon signs in a busy city. Moving so fast it's almost a blur. Forming into something greater than the sum of its parts.

metadata.name: CA Monti #61
metadata.description:
As a sequel of previous collection CA Vista but with a completely different approach, CA Monti intends to explore landscape generation through the use of Stephen Wolfram's cellular automata.

Press 'S' to download.

metadata.name: Celebrate the D2 #404
metadata.description:
Fixed a bug in the original project.
It can now actually output uniform patterns :-)
 
A fun free mint to celebrate 500 followers on Twitter.
The project is open for 24 hours, for all to mint.
And after that, the remaining editions get burned.

The base shape is a "super ellipse", made famous by (among others) danish inventor and polymath Piet Hein.

metadata.name: GE-I #447
metadata.description:
The first in a series of grid experiments.

Made of simple expressions of shape, color, and layout. There are 10 features including 32 pallets & 34 shape sets. The base grid is constructed of either 2x2, 4x4, 6x6, 8x8, or 20x20 layouts.
